	<xsl:template match="/" name="LPL-AMEND-IL">
		<fo:block>
			<xsl:call-template name="CommonHeader" />
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block text-align="center" margin-left="1.3in"
			margin-right="1.3in" font-size="12px"
			font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;"
			space-before="7mm" space-after="7mm" font-weight="bold">

			ILLINOIS AMENDATORY ENDORSEMENT

		</fo:block>
		<fo:block padding-left="5pt"
			font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;"
			font-size="10px" text-align="justify">

			<fo:block space-after="4mm">
				In consideration of the premium
				charged, it is agreed that:
			</fo:block>

<fo:block space-after="4mm">
<fo:list-block>

	<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
			<fo:block>
				<fo:inline>1.	</fo:inline>
			</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body>
			<fo:block start-indent="7mm">
					<fo:block space-after="4mm">
						Section III., Extension of Coverage B., Spousal and Domestic Partner Extension, 
						is amended by deleting the phrase “lawful spouse or lawful domestic partner” and 
						replacing it with “lawful spouse, lawful domestic partner or party to a civil union 
						recognized under Illinois law”.
					</fo:block>
					
		</fo:block>
	</fo:list-item-body>
</fo:list-item>
<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
	<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			<fo:inline>2.	</fo:inline>
		</fo:block>
	</fo:list-item-label>
	<fo:list-item-body>
		<fo:block start-indent="7mm">
<fo:block space-after="4mm">
	Section III., Extension of Coverage D., Extended Reporting Period Extensions, is amended as follows:
</fo:block>
<fo:block>

	<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
			<fo:list-item-label>
				<fo:block start-indent="7mm">
					a.
				</fo:block>
			</fo:list-item-label>
			<fo:list-item-body>
			<fo:block start-indent="14mm" space-after="4mm">
			Subsection 1., Automatic Extended Reporting Period, is amended by deletion of the phrase 
			“other than for cancellation for nonpayment of premium or for nonpayment of Deductible due hereunder”.
			</fo:block>
				</fo:list-item-body>
				</fo:list-item>
				<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
				<fo:list-item-label>
				<fo:block start-indent="7mm">
				b.
				</fo:block>
				</fo:list-item-label>
				<fo:list-item-body>
				<fo:block start-indent="14mm" space-after="4mm">
				Subsection 2., Optional Extended Reporting Period, is amended by deletion of the phrase 
				“other than for nonpayment of premium or for the nonpayment of Deductible due hereunder”.
				</fo:block>
				</fo:list-item-body>
				</fo:list-item>
				<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
				<fo:list-item-label>
				<fo:block start-indent="7mm">
				c.
				</fo:block>
				</fo:list-item-label>
				<fo:list-item-body start-indent="14mm">
				<fo:block space-after="4mm">
				Subsection 3., Non-Practicing Extended Reporting Period, subsection (c), Non-Practicing 
				Extended Reporting Period Limits of Liability, is deleted and replaced with the following:
				</fo:block>
				<fo:list-block>
				<fo:list-item>
				<fo:list-item-label>
				<fo:block start-indent="14mm">
				<fo:inline font-weight="bold">
				(c)
				</fo:inline>
				</fo:block>
				</fo:list-item-label>
				<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
				<fo:block space-after="4mm">
				<fo:inline font-weight="bold">
				Non-Practicing Extended Reporting Period Limits of Liability
				</fo:inline>
				</fo:block>
				<fo:block space-after="4mm">
				The <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer’s</fo:inline> Limit of Liability for all 
				<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Claims</fo:inline> first made against an 
				<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insured</fo:inline> during any Non-Practicing Extended Reporting Period will be part of, 
				and not in addition to, the Limit of Liability shown in Item 3. of the Declarations, 
				regardless of the number of Non-Practicing Extended Reporting Periods purchased.
				</fo:block>
				</fo:list-item-body>
				</fo:list-item>
				</fo:list-block>
				</fo:list-item-body>
				</fo:list-item>
				<fo:list-item>
				<fo:list-item-label>
				<fo:block start-indent="7mm">
				d.
				</fo:block>
				</fo:list-item-label>
				<fo:list-item-body start-indent="14mm">
				<fo:block  space-after="4mm">
				Subsection 4., Conditions for Extended Reporting Periods, is deleted and replaced with the following:
				</fo:block>
				<fo:list-block>
				<fo:list-item>
				<fo:list-item-label>
				<fo:block start-indent="14mm">
				<fo:inline font-weight="bold">
				4.
				</fo:inline>
				</fo:block>
				</fo:list-item-label>
				<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
				<fo:block space-after="4mm">
				<fo:inline font-weight="bold">
				Conditions for Extended Reporting Periods
				</fo:inline>
				</fo:block>
				<fo:block>
				As a condition precedent to the right to elect an Extended Reporting Period:
				</fo:block>
				<fo:list-block space-after="4mm">
				<fo:list-item>
				<fo:list-item-label>
				<fo:block start-indent="21mm">
				(a)
				</fo:block>
				</fo:list-item-label>
				<fo:list-item-body>
				<fo:block start-indent="28mm">
				all <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insureds</fo:inline> must be in compliance with the terms and conditions of the policy;
				</fo:block>
				</fo:list-item-body>
				</fo:list-item>
				<fo:list-item>
				<fo:list-item-label>
				<fo:block start-indent="21mm">
				(b)
				</fo:block>
				</fo:list-item-label>
				<fo:list-item-body>
				<fo:block start-indent="28mm">
				the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured’s</fo:inline> right to practice law 
				has not been revoked, suspended or surrendered 
				at the request of any regulatory authority for reasons other than death, disability or 
				retirement; and
				</fo:block>
				</fo:list-item-body>
				</fo:list-item>
				<fo:list-item>
				<fo:list-item-label>
				<fo:block start-indent="21mm">
				(c)
				</fo:block>
				</fo:list-item-label>
				<fo:list-item-body>
				<fo:block start-indent="28mm">
				the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> provides 
				the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> with written notice of its selection and 
				pays the premium charge, and any other monies due and owing the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline>, 
				if applicable, for the selected Extended Reporting Period in full within 60 
				days of the expiration date of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Policy Period</fo:inline>.
				</fo:block>
				</fo:list-item-body>
				</fo:list-item>
				</fo:list-block>
				<fo:block>
				This right to elect an Extended Reporting Period shall lapse unless the provisions of 
				(a) through (c) in the preceding paragraph are fully met.
				</fo:block>
				</fo:list-item-body>
				</fo:list-item>
				</fo:list-block>
				</fo:list-item-body>
				</fo:list-item>
				</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		</fo:block>
	</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
		3.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="7mm">
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
		Section IV., Definition E., <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Damages</fo:inline>, is amended as follows:
		</fo:block>
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block start-indent="7mm">
		a.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="14mm">
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
		The first sentence is deleted and replaced with the following:
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
		<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Damages</fo:inline> means a monetary judgment (including pre- and post-judgment 
		interest awarded against the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insured</fo:inline>), monetary award or monetary 
		settlement negotiated with the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer’s</fo:inline> written consent; 
		however, any payments made for pre- and post-judgment interest will be in addition to 
		the Limit of Liability.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
	</fo:list-block>
</fo:block>
						<fo:block margin-top="2.5cm"/>
						<fo:block font-size="9px" color="grey" text-align="left">
						LPL-AMEND-IL (04/17)&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;
						&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;
						&#160;&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;&#160;&#160; &#160;&#160; &#160;
						&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;
						&#160;&#160;&#160; &#160;&#160; &#160;&#160;&#160; &#160;&#160; &#160;
						&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;&#160;&#160; &#160;&#160; &#160;
						&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;&#160;
						&#160;&#160; &#160;&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;&#160; &#160;&#160; &#160;&#160;&#160; &#160;&#160; &#160; Page 1 of 3
					</fo:block>
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block page-break-after="always"></fo:block>
		
		<fo:block padding-left="5pt"
			font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;"
			font-size="10px" text-align="justify">
			
			<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			<fo:list-block>
			<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
			<fo:list-item-label>
			<fo:block start-indent="7mm">
			b.
			</fo:block>
			</fo:list-item-label>
			<fo:list-item-body start-indent="14mm">
			<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			Paragraph 3. is deleted and replaced with the following:
			</fo:block>
			<fo:list-block>
			<fo:list-item>
			<fo:list-item-label>
			<fo:block start-indent="14mm">
			3.
			</fo:block>
			</fo:list-item-label>
			<fo:list-item-body>
			<fo:block start-indent="21mm">
			punitive or exemplary damages, awards or judgments or any amounts which are a multiple 
			of compensatory damages, awards or judgments assessed as a result of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insured’s</fo:inline> own 
			misconduct; except that if a suit shall have been brought against the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insured</fo:inline> with respect 
			to a <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Claim</fo:inline> for acts or alleged acts falling within the coverage hereof, seeking both 
			compensatory and punitive or exemplary damages, then the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> will afford a defense 
			to such action without liability, however, for such punitive or exemplary damages;
			</fo:block>
			</fo:list-item-body>
			</fo:list-item>
			</fo:list-block>
			</fo:list-item-body>
			</fo:list-item>
			
			<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
			<fo:list-item-label>
			<fo:block>
			4.
			</fo:block>
			</fo:list-item-label>
			<fo:list-item-body start-indent="7mm">
			<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			Section IV., Definition H., <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Immediate Family Member</fo:inline>, paragraph 6., 
			is deleted and replaced with the following:
			</fo:block>
			<fo:list-block>
			<fo:list-item>
			<fo:list-item-label>
			<fo:block start-indent="14mm">
			6.
			</fo:block>
			</fo:list-item-label>
			<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
			<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			past or present spouse or party to a civil union recognized under Illinois law,
			</fo:block>
			</fo:list-item-body>
			</fo:list-item>
			</fo:list-block>
			</fo:list-item-body>
			</fo:list-item>
			
			<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
			<fo:list-item-label>
			<fo:block>
			5.
			</fo:block>
			</fo:list-item-label>
			<fo:list-item-body start-indent="7mm">
			<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			Section VI., General Condition D., Cancellation and Nonrenewal, is deleted and replaced with the following:
			</fo:block>
			<fo:list-block>
			<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
			<fo:list-item-label>
			<fo:block start-indent="7mm">
			<fo:inline font-weight="bold">
			D.
			</fo:inline>
			</fo:block>
			</fo:list-item-label>
			<fo:list-item-body start-indent="14mm">
			<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			Cancellation, Nonrenewal and Conditional Renewal
			</fo:block>
			<fo:list-block>
			<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
			<fo:list-item-label>
			<fo:block start-indent="14mm">
			<fo:inline font-weight="bold">
			1.
			</fo:inline>
			</fo:block>
			</fo:list-item-label>
			<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
			<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			<fo:inline font-weight="bold">
			Cancellation
			</fo:inline>
			</fo:block>
			<fo:list-block>
					<fo:list-item>
						<fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:block start-indent="21mm">
								<fo:inline>(a)</fo:inline>
							</fo:block>
						</fo:list-item-label>
						<fo:list-item-body>
							<fo:block start-indent="28mm">
								The <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> may cancel this policy at any time prior to 
								the expiration date of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Policy Period</fo:inline> by providing 
								prior written notice to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> or by surrender 
								of this policy to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> or its authorized agent.  
								If the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> cancels this policy, the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> 
								shall return 90% of the unearned portion of the premium.
							</fo:block>
							<fo:block margin-top="4mm"></fo:block>
						</fo:list-item-body>
					</fo:list-item>

					<fo:list-item>
						<fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:block start-indent="21mm">
								<fo:inline>(b)</fo:inline>
							</fo:block>
						</fo:list-item-label>
						<fo:list-item-body>
							<fo:block start-indent="28mm">
								<fo:block space-after="4mm">
									The <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> may only cancel this policy for nonpayment of premium.  
									This policy may be canceled by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> by mailing to 
									the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline>, at the last mailing address known by 
									the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline>, written notice of cancellation at least 10 days 
									before the effective date of cancellation.  Such notice shall include a specific 
									explanation of the reason for cancellation and the effective date of 
									cancellation stated in such notice shall become the expiration date of the 
									<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Policy Period</fo:inline>.  The <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> shall maintain proof of 
									mailing of such notice on a recognized U.S. Post Office form or a form acceptable to 
									the U.S. Post Office or other commercial mail delivery service.  A copy of such 
									notice shall be sent to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured’s</fo:inline> broker 
									if known, or the agent of record, if known, at the last mailing address known to 
									the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline>.  The <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured’s</fo:inline> broker or 
									the agent of record may opt to accept notification electronically.  
									If the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> cancels this policy, the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> 
									shall credit the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> the pro rata unearned portion 
									of the premium.  Payment or tender of any unearned premium by 
									the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> shall not be a condition precedent to 
									the effectiveness of cancellation, but such payment shall be made as soon as practicable.
								</fo:block>

							</fo:block>
							
						</fo:list-item-body>
					</fo:list-item>

				</fo:list-block>
			</fo:list-item-body>
			</fo:list-item>
			
			<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
			<fo:list-item-label>
			<fo:block start-indent="14mm">
			<fo:inline font-weight="bold">
			2.
			</fo:inline>
			</fo:block>
			</fo:list-item-label>
			<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
			<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Nonrenewal</fo:inline>
			</fo:block>
			<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			This policy may be nonrenewed by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> by mailing to 
			the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline>, at the last mailing address known by 
			the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline>, written notice of nonrenewal at least 60 days prior to 
			the expiration date of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Policy Period</fo:inline>.  Such notice shall 
			provide a specific explanation of the reasons for nonrenewal.  
			The <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> shall maintain proof of mailing of such notice 
			on a recognized U.S. Post Office form or a form acceptable to the U.S. 
			Post Office or other commercial mail delivery service.  An exact and unaltered copy of 
			such notice shall also be sent to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured’s</fo:inline> producer, 
			if known, or the producer of record.  The <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured’s</fo:inline> 
			producer or the producer of record may opt to accept notification electronically.
			</fo:block>
			<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			The <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> may not extend the current <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Policy Period</fo:inline> for 
			purposes of providing notice of its intention not to renew.  
			If the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> has failed to provide such notice, 
			it shall renew the expiring policy under the same terms and conditions for an additional year 
			or until the effective date of any similar insurance is procured by 
			the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline>, whichever is earlier.  
			The <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> may increase the renewal premium.  
			However, such increase must be less than 30% of the expiring term’s premium and 
			notice of such increase must be delivered to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> 
			on or before the date of expiration of the current <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Policy Period</fo:inline>.
			</fo:block>
			</fo:list-item-body>
			</fo:list-item>
			
			<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
			<fo:list-item-label>
			<fo:block start-indent="14mm">
			<fo:inline font-weight="bold">
			3.
			</fo:inline>
			</fo:block>
			</fo:list-item-label>
			<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
			<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			<fo:inline font-weight="bold">
			Conditional Renewal
			</fo:inline>
			</fo:block>
			<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			If the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> intends to renew this policy with an increase in 
			premium of 30% or more or with changes in the Deductible or coverage that materially alter 
			the policy shall mail or deliver to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> 
			written notice of such increase or change in the Deductible or coverage at least 60 days prior 
			to the renewal date.  If the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> has failed to provide 
			such notice at least 60 days prior to the renewal date, but does so no less than 31 days prior 
			to the renewal date, the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> may extend the current policy 
			at the current terms and
			</fo:block>
			</fo:list-item-body>
			</fo:list-item>
			</fo:list-block>
			</fo:list-item-body>
			</fo:list-item>
			</fo:list-block>
			</fo:list-item-body>
			</fo:list-item>
			
			</fo:list-block>
			
			</fo:block>
			<fo:block margin-top="2cm"/>
						<fo:block font-size="9px" color="grey" text-align="left">
						LPL-AMEND-IL (04/17)&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;
